Here is a script using HTML for the form and PHP for saving the data. You will need a web server with PHP installed to run this.

**1. Create a file named `index.html`:**

This file contains the form that the user will see.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Text Input Form</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>Enter Text to Save</h2>

    <form action="save.php" method="post">
        <textarea name="user_text" rows="10" cols="50" required></textarea>
        <br>
        <input type="submit" value="Save Text">
    </form>

</body>
</html>
```

**2. Create a file named `save.php` in the same directory:**

This script receives the text from the form and saves it to a file named `data.txt`.

```php
<?php
// Check if the form was submitted using the POST method
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {

    // Check if the 'user_text' field is not empty
    if (!empty($_POST['user_text'])) {

        // Get the text from the textarea
        $text_to_save = $_POST['user_text'];

        // Specify the file to save to
        $file = 'data.txt';

        // Append the new text to the file, adding a newline character
        // FILE_APPEND prevents overwriting the file's existing content
        // LOCK_EX prevents others from writing to the file at the same time
        file_put_contents($file, $text_to_save . PHP_EOL, FILE_APPEND | LOCK_EX);

        echo "Text saved successfully!";
        echo '<br><a href="index.html">Go back</a>';

    } else {
        echo "Error: Text field was empty.";
    }
} else {
    // Handle cases where the script is accessed directly without a POST request
    echo "Invalid request method.";
}
?>
```

When you submit the form, the text will be appended to a file named `data.txt` in the same directory.
